condition1: Sensing Avg. | Axb|>11.792 (1.2) m/s2 over 5 consecutive samples @ 10
event_description: Sensing Avg. Axb > 11.892 m/s2 over 5 consecutive samples @ 10 ms

condition2: 3 consecutive samples @ 10 of DIP 30==1 & DIP 31==0 (OOC1) DIP 32==1 & DIP 33==0 (OOC2) DIP 34==1 & DIP 35==0 (OOC3) DIP 36==1 & DIP 37==0 (OOC4) Of CCSC using following logic
event_description: Out-Off-Canister is sensed by 4 OOC sensors and declared using 2/4 logic by OBC. For normal pyro channel arming ½ logic is used by taking the status OOC1,OOC2(Diagonally opposite) For Redundant pyro channel arming ½ logic is used by taking the status of OOC3,OOC4 H0 is the Lift-off height.
Pyro normal command is issued for BD separation and diversion through DSM. 500msec delay is given to get sufficient clearance from canister top.
Pyro repeat command is issued for BD separation and diversion
Pyro normal command is withdrawn for BD separation and diversion
Pyro repeat command is issued for BD separation and diversion

condition2: 3 consecutive samples @ 10 of CCSC DIP # 24,26,12,13 using 2/4 logic
event_description: On-Board separation is sensed through a relay/loop back signal
Issue null command to both FNC actuators and switch on the contactor supply of FNC actuators. First Null commands to be issued then contactor to be made ON through normal Channel
Issue null command to both FNC actuators and switch on the contactor supply of FNC actuators. First Null commands to be issued then contactor to be made ON through repeat Channel
Issue null command to all 4 ADC actuators and switch on the contactors supply of ADC actuators. First Null commands to be issued then contactor to be made ON through normal Channel
Issue null command to all 4 ADC actuators and switch on the contactors supply of ADC actuators. First Null commands to be issued then contactor to be made ON through repeat Channel
Contactor L1 FNC ON normal command is withdrawn
Contactor L1 ON repeat command is withdrawn
Contactor ADC ON normal command is withdrawn
Contactor ADC ON repeat command is withdrawn
Ignite L1 rocket motor through normal channel
Ignite L1 rocket motor through repeat channel
L1 ignition normal command is withdrawn
L1 ignition repeat command is withdrawn
Start control in three channels. Pitch and yaw through FNC and roll through ADC
Stop L1 TVC, this is purely a software command. Switch OFF ADC roll control.
Register L1 Tail OFF
Withdraw Normal Channel Stage1 Stage seperation
Withdraw repeat Channel Stage1 Stage seperation
L1 seperation sensing by sampling 3 consecutive samples @10 ms and using 2/4 logic or with 500ms backup time logic.
Start GV attitude control through ADC
L2 Motor Pyro Fire through normal channel with dynamic delay. This delay is function of range and L1 motor performance
L2 Motor Pyro firing through repeat channel
Withdraw L2 motor pyro pulse through normal channel
Withdraw L2 motor pyro pulse through repeat channel
Register L2 tail OFF
Normal command to switch ON seeker system Seeker Power ON time to impact time should not be more than 220 s(Battery limitation)
Normal command to switch ON seeker system is withdrawn
Heat shield separation Initially T_IGPhase4 set to 1000sec and it will reset by guidance algorithm during terminal phase R_go is 60.0 m
Command for HS pyro-pusher
HS pyro bolt command withdrawn
HS pyro pusher command withdrawn
HS separation sensing by sampling 3 consecutive samples @10ms and using 2/2 logic
Warhead arming is done 100msec after HS separation sensing. Prior to this OBC to issue OBC 3 command to SAM through RS422.
Warhead arming repeat command is issued after normal command
h: Missile INS altitude RA Transmitter ON to be initiated when missile altitude <= 7000.0 m.
h: Missile INS altitude Warhead detonation Command
Warhead detonation N Command Withdraw

event_description: Sensing of lift off by OBC (Negative Logic – i.e. values will change from “1” to “0”)

condition2: OOC Sensing: (3 consecutive samples @ 10 of 3 OOC’s DIP@ 0,1,2 using 2/3 logic)
event_description: Out of canister sensing by OBC: Negative Logic- i.e values will change from “1” to “0”
condition3: 3 consecutive samples @ 10 of DIP# 6,7 of MIU-1 using 2/2 logic

event_description: Ignition command to BM! From OBC through normal. Additionally BM1 ignition command issued by LC via secondary unbilical through delayed pyro as a backup firing command to cater for failure modes & emergency launch. IN addition to this , one more BM1 ignition command is issued through electronic timer triggered by OOC signal as a backup firing command to cater for failure modes & emergency launch(ref. section 1.3)
Ignition command to BM1 from OBC through redundant.
Withdrawal of BM1 ignition normal command.
Withdrawal of BM1 ignition redundant command.

condition1: (T>=(TOOC +0.200+ TGFUF_Delay )) TGFUF_Delay_calculated_by_guidance_for_platform launch(ref. Appendix B) TGFUF_Delay==0.000 for Ground launch TGFUF_Delay==0.100 for Pontoon Launch
event_description: Firing of Frid Fin(GF) unfolding through normal. Adaptive GFUF delay disabled in group/pontoon launches and small fixed delay used to unfold GF early in air/water as there is no significant missile attitude divergence is expected in these missions.
Firing of Grid Fin(GF) unfolding through redundant.

Withdraw of redundant ignition command to APUCM.
Sensing BD Tail – Off Through acceleration sensing Backup time of 7.0s is given in case of failure to detect BD tail-off.

Withdraw normal channel BD separation command
Withdraw redundant channel BD separation command
